{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17500949","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17500949"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:20:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:20:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1699"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1699","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1699"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.86,0.11,0.02,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1699"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90288"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1699","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1699"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1699"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74541"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2602"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4487"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"10964"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"237"},{"type":"contributions","id":"30959"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42372"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90288","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/90288"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 56-year-old man presents with a three week history of increasing shortness of breath on exertion, orthopnoea and fatigue. On examination, an S3 gallop rhythm is present. There is jugular venous distension, peripheral oedema, basal crackles on auscultation of both lung bases. The ECG shows a low limb lead voltage, wide QRS complexes and left bundle branch block. P mitrale is present. The chest X-ray shows an enlarged cardiac shadow.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate investigation to confirm the diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Complete blood count","Transthoracic echocardiogram","Brain natriuretic peptide level","Cardiac MRI","99mTc Sestamibi scan"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u2019s clinical picture is consistent with an acute exacerbation of heart failure, and so the most appropriate investigation would be a \u003Cstrong\u003Etransthoracic echocardiogram\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHeart failure affects approximately half a million Australians, and is associated with a high morbidity and mortality, frequent hospitalisation and a massive cost to the health care system. Heart failure can manifest in many forms, including acute decompensation (including acute pulmonary oedema), chronic systolic failure (heart failure with reduced ejection fraction) and chronic diastolic failure (heart failure with preserved ejection fraction).\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe aetiology of heart failure is most commonly an ischaemic event leading to left ventricular dysfunction. Other causes, which may be linked to ischaemia include valvular heart disease, chronic arrhythmia, thyroid disease or HIV. Symptoms are variable and overlap with many other conditions. Non-specific symptoms of exertional dyspnoea, orthopnoea, paroxysmal nocturnal dyspnoea, fatigue and weakness are common. Diagnostic testing may involve ECG, chest X-ray and blood examination, specifically measurement of B-type natriuretic peptide (BNP). However the echocardiogram is the definitive diagnostic test for heart failure, which provides information regarding ventricular size and function, as well as determining the aetiology through the identification of valvular pathology or areas of previous infarction.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A transthoracic echocardiogram will help quantify information on ventricular size and function in patients with heart failure."],"references":["Krum H, Driscoll A. Management of heart failure. Medical Journal of Australia. 2013;199(5):334-9."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74541"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1699"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74541","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/74541"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-13T16:20:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-13T16:20:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1699"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90288"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"65","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/65"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Investigations","syno